  "texts": [
    "Based on this idea, we might want to construct a prior π that gives a large weight to the relevant parameters, that is, to parameters such that R(θ) is small.",
    "A possible prior is π -βR for some β > 0, where π -βR is given by dπ -βR dπ (θ) = e -βR(θ)",
    "E ϑ∼π [e -βR(ϑ) ].",
    "This priori is often refered to as a localized prior (Catoni, 2003; Catoni, 2007) or as a distribution-dependent prior (Lever et al., 2010; Lever et al., 2013).",
    "This choice is not data-dependent, and thus allowed by theory."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This priori is often refered to as a localized prior (Catoni, 2003; Catoni, 2007) or as a distribution-dependent prior (Lever et al., 2010; Lever et al., 2013)."
  ]
}